comments: Wood (DET) doesn't maintain legal guarding position when he makes contact with Randle's (NYK) arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) makes contact to Maker's (DET) arm during the rebound.
Jackson (DET) moves along Payton's (NYK) path and makes marginal contact during his driving shot attempt.
Jackson (DET) makes marginal contact with his off-arm to Bullock (NYK) and doesn't affect his ability to defend.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact with Maker (DET), but doesn't fully extend his arm during the rebound.
Jackson (DET) makes marginal contact with Payton (NYK) as he makes contact with the ball during the rebound.
Payton (NYK) gathers the ball and takes a legal step. He then maintains his pivot foot.
Ellington (NYK) loses control of the ball and legally regathers it. He then maintains his pivot prior to his pass.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact with Jackson (DET) under the basket and doesn't affect his ability to get to the long rebound.
Brown (DET) makes marginal contact with Randle (NYK) as he dislodges the ball during the rebound.
Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Snell (DET) firms up and delivers legal contact.
Jackson (DET) has a legal resting hand on  the upper body of Payton (NYK) that slides off as he enters his shooting motion.
Randle (NYK) and Wood (DET) engage and disengage during the rebound.
Randle (NYK) clears space unnaturally and delivers contact to Maker's (DET) head that affects his ability to defend.
Henson (DET) firms up in Ntilikina's (NYK) path and gives him room to avoid the screen.
Wood (DET) firms up in Ntilikina's (NYK) path and gives him room to avoid the screen.
Robinson (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Wood (DET).
Snell (DET) commits a take foul on Bullock (NYK).
Robinson (NYK) makes marginal contact with Jackson (DET) during the inbound.
Ntilikina (NYK) briefly engages in arm contact with Galloway (DET) as he is trying to get around the screen.
Payton (NYK) makes marginal contact with Jackson (DET) and doesn't affect his ability to rebound.
